Sentencas: A yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) layer (similar to 2 mu m) is fabricated by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) technique on an Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte film which is prepared by a co-pressing process on a NiO-SDC anode substrate.
Titulo: Performance improvement of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia as an electronic blocking layer by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: La0.8Sr02MnO3-delta-YSZ (LSM-YSZ, 70:30 wt.%) cathode is applied onto the SDC/YSZ bilayer electrolytes to form a single cell.
Titulo: Performance improvement of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia as an electronic blocking layer by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The open circuit voltages of the cell increase significantly compared with that of the SDC single electrolyte cell.
Titulo: Performance improvement of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia as an electronic blocking layer by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: Preparation of an SDC buffer layer (similar to 500 nm) on the bilayer electrolytes by PLD method is also studied for reducing the cathode polarization losses with a Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta-SDC (SSC-SDC, 70:30 wt.%) cathode and preventing the interfacial chemical reaction between YSZ and SSC.
Titulo: Performance improvement of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia as an electronic blocking layer by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The YSZ thin film blocks electrical current leakage in the SDC layer, whereas the SDC buffer layer with the SSC-SDC cathode decreases the cathode polarization losses, which results in the overall enhanced performance.
Titulo: Performance improvement of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia as an electronic blocking layer by pulsed laser deposition
